text: From arrival to departure the whole experience was amazing. The check in was very easy and the welcome drink was delicious (we arrived late at night so our welcome drink came the next day but it was still really nice). The rooms are a good size and the smell of incense floats through the jungle canopy. Beds very comfy and clean, bathrooms nice too. There is a safe in the room. The pool area is very nice with the infinity pool overlooking the jungle. There are single and couple pool beds. Whilst there is no pool bar, you can order drinks on WhatsApp and they bring it out to you - you can pay in cash or charge it to your room. The restaurant is amazing - the breakfast allows you to choose 1 hot drink, I juice and 1 breakfast option that ranges from savoury, sweet, contemporary, Indonesian and international cuisine. Best coffee I’ve ever had in all of Asia (except maybe Vietnam). The dinner is also incredible so we ended up eating there twice. The staff are very friendly and hospitable which is standard across Asia. I cannot fault their efforts to make our stay relaxing and comfortable. Suitable for couples, families and anyone looking for that “eat, pray, love” experience.
title: Eat, Pray, Love in Ubud - Incredible!

text: My fiancé and I stayed at the Dinara for 4 nights. We booked here last minute, let’s just say the photos do not do it justice. The reception and welcome drinks on arrival were amazing and everyone was extremely accommodating and kind. We were shown to our room, walking past the mini rice field and led along a organic curving path between the bamboo and lush plants. There is incense burning all the time which fills the air with a delishous sent which won’t be forgotten. The room itself was perfection, the spacious balcony, huge comfortable bed and luxurious bathroom were dreamy. Everything has attention to detail, from bathrobes to USB charging points everything has been thought of. We also made use of the spa and pool areas. The spa was lovely, we had facials, full body massages and the sunburn recovery treatment which was my favourite, for cooling our hot skin! Highly recommend. The pool is also amazing with fresh towels, day beds and food and drinks service throughout. WiFi and usual services all worked smoothly. Restaurant along side hotel was also delish! We highly recommend to have a stay here, it is very underrated as it has only been open 2 years so it definitely deserves more attention!

This hotel was the best choice in Ubud. The employees take good care of everything, including the plants which are exactely as in photos. It is located in a calm area of Ubud, 7 min by car or 30 min walking to Ubud Center which is very crowded and noisy. We went twice in Ubud Center with Gojek app which is better than GoCab app. We choose the suite with balcony which is a big room with a big bathroom and balcony. The room has a fridge which can’t be seen in photos because it is integrated in the furniture. It was very clean, we had our room cleaned every day. We had water provider by the employees every morning and at about 18:00 a guy came to ask us if we need more water and if we want our towels to be changed. There is a restaurant area above the pool area and a yoga area above the restaurant. There was a yoga class saturday which was very nice. text:
This is one of the nicest hotels I've stayed at in a while. To begin with, the staff are extremely kind and caring. They remember your name, they know your requests and when you stay somewhat longer (11 days in our case), they start anticipating your requests beforehand. They inquire about the quality of your stay, how your room is and whether anything can be done to improve your stay. They make you feel at home. 

The room we stayed in (Dinara Suite) is very nice and cozy. The bathroom was amazing, with a huge shower and awesome water pressure (which can be a thing in Ubud) and a gigantic bath. They gave all the sanitation utensils you would need in a bathroom and a blow-dryer that was actually useful to dry clothes with from the rain (travel hack). The airconditioning was good and the staff provided a dehumidifier machine daily for when it had rained heavily and it got a little humid. 

The pool and cowork (soon to be another restaurant)  are awesome and the lounge beds are great. The attention to detail everywhere is noticed and appreciated. The restaurant is quite amazing too. The staff there are attentive and remember your preferences. We for example had specific requests for smoothies and dishes, and they remembered them fairly quickly. The food is delicious, freshly made with very good ingredients and very reasonably priced. We loved the included breakfastcl and our dinners there. 

Our stay here was amazing. The only con is that there are some roosters and chickens that start their morning routine pretty early, at like 4:30-5:00 am. Which can be a thing for light sleepers. We sort of got used to it after a week, but you're still aware of it.
title: A great little oasis in Ubud that we loved

My best friend and I spent 7 days together in Ubud at the Dinara Hotel.

First of all we were totally flashed by the friendliness of the staff. At any time they were so helpful, suitcases were carried to the room and we were given a small room tour when we moved into the room. Day and night the front desk was manned by at least 2 people.

The hotel is a beautiful small complex with jungle vibes.
The pool has a beautiful jungle view and there were always many sunbeds and canopy beds free, so that no one has to get the idea to reserve a sunbed with a towel.

The rooms are very lovingly furnished and clean. Due to the generally very high humidity in Ubud, the beds are a bit wet, which takes some getting used to at the beginning. But that can not be avoided in Ubud with such high humidity!

The breakfast in the neighboring Café Melali is the best breakfast I have ever enjoyed on vacation.

The hotel can only be recommended, we have enjoyed our vacation here to the fullest.
title: Charming small hotel with jungle vibes

This hotel delivers so much that’s needed for a traveller exploring Bali. There is a beautiful, calming, atmosphere here provided by the incredibly helpful, friendly, staff as well as the beautiful greenery throughout the hotel.

Room service is very efficient and convenient providing a good drinks and food menu from the lovely restaurant below. 

The location is great, out of the way of any noise and with a lovely 20(ish) minute stroll downhill towards Ubud or scoot there in 5 mins. 

I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone looking for affordable luxury in Bali. You will not regret it!

text:
Das Dinara Hotel Ubud ist ein absolut wunderschönes Hotel mit Wohlfühlcharakter. Wir hatten eigentlich das Gartenzimmer gebucht, haben beim einchecken jedoch ein Upgrade bekommen für ein größeres Zimmer mit Balkon. Danke Wayan für das tolle Upgrade. 
Das Badezimmer war riesig und mit einer schönen großen Badewanne und einer großen Dusche ausgestattet. Der Ausblick vom Balkon ins Grüne war traumhaft. 
Das Frühstück im Hotelrestaurant war mit Abstand das Beste, was wir während unseres 4 wöchigen Aufenthalts in Indonesien hatten. Auf Sauberkeit wird penibel geachtet. 
Die Hotelanlage ist sehr schön mit einem tollen Infinity Pool. Einen Yoga Raum mit einer wundervollen Aussicht bietet das Hotel ebenfalls. 
Das Personal war sehr freundlich und bei Fragen immer hilfsbereit. Unser Aufenthalt mit unserem 11 Monate alten Baby war sehr positiv. Uns wurde kostenfrei ein Babybett gebracht und das Restaurant hat uns jedes Mal ein Babystuhl bereitgestellt. Wir wir festgestellt haben, leider nicht selbstverständlich auf Bali. Für die Familienfreundlichkeit daher ein extra Lob an das Hotel- und Restaurantpersonal. 

Insgesamt war es für uns das beste Hotel auf unserer Reise, wo das Preis-Leistungsverhältnis mehr als stimmt. Es ist zudem auch viel schöner als auf den Bildern dargestellt. Wir würden das Hotel daher jedem zu 100% weiterempfehlen und auf jeden Fall wiederkommen.
title: Wunderschönes Hotel zum Entspannen

text:
Wir wurden in diesem Hotel mit äußerst großer Herzlichkeit aufgenommen. 

Nicht nur dass die Zimmer toll ausgestattet sind, (uns hat vor allem auch der riesige Balkon und das großzügige Bad begeistert), auch die insgesamt sehr gepflegte üppig begrünte Anlage und der tolle Poolbereich haben uns begeistert.

Wenn doch mal Fragen offen waren, so haben Wayan und sein Team diese immer schnell und herzlich gelöst, so dass wir uns bald eher gefühlt haben als wären wir bei Freunden zu Gast als in einem anonymen Hotel. (Was letztlich dazu geführt hat dass wir noch mal um fünf Nächte verlängert haben)

Absolut auch erwähnenswert: das zum Hotel gehörige Restaurant Melali.

Kreative indonesische Cross-over Küche, eine sensationelle Frühstückskarte, volle Cocktail und Getränkeauswahl und auch hier wieder ein außergewöhnlich freundliche und aufmerksame Belegschaft.

Meine Nummer eins für Ubud!
title: Wunderbares Gesamtpaket

text:
Das ganze Team und insbesondere der hotel Manager sind sehr freundlich sehr zuvorkommend und lesen einem wirklich jeden Wunsch von den Lippen ab. Nicht nur gute Service sondern auch interessante Informationen über die Region oder Ausflugsziele werden gerne geteilt das Hotel verfügt über einen sehr schönen Pool und ein wunderbares Restaurant. Da wirklich schon viele Hotels gesehen und auch viel erlebt aber so etwas wie hier so freundlich so positiv wirklich schon lange nicht mehr. Ich wurde freundlich gefragt ob ich eine Bewertung über das Hotel abgebe da ich sehr zufrieden bin und alles hervorragend war habe ich es auch natürlich gerne gemacht. 

Von mir somit eine absolut positive Bewertung und eine Empfehlung für ein kleines Hotel mit absoluten Luxus neuen Zimmern neue Anlage und sehr freundlichen Personal.
title: Der Service ist herausragend so was habe ich schon lange nicht mehr erlebt!!

text:
Abbiamo soggiornato in coppia in questa struttura per 5 giorni nel mese di agosto.
L’hotel si trova a nord di Ubud, fuori dal caos cittadino ma comodo per tutti i movimenti noleggiando un motorino(mezzo consigliato).
Il complesso è molto recente e le camere sono spaziose e dotate di tutti i comfort.
Ad uso comune c’è una piscina che da sulla foresta appena davanti è una sala dedicata allo yoga al secondo piano, anche questa esposta verso la vegetazione.
Lo staff e il manager sono persone deliziose che non ci hanno fanno mancare nulla per trascorrere un piacevole soggiorno.
Ci hanno organizzato delle escursioni, messo in contatto con il noleggio motorino e dato consigli molto utili per poter vivere al meglio la meravigliosa Bali.
Da aggiungere a tutto ciò un ottimo ristorante che, dalla colazione alla cena, ci ha proposto dei piatti salutari e gustosi.
Infine abbiamo usufruito della spa per un massaggio molto rigenerante. Questo servizio dovrebbe essere più incentivato dalla struttura che invece ce l’ha comunicato solo su richiesta.
In conclusione non avrei dubbi sul consigliarlo a chiunque per un bellissimo ricordo de “l’isola degli dei”.
title: Paradiso a Ubud

text: Heel blij om in Dinara Hotel te mogen overnachten! We werden hartelijk verwelkomt met een drankje. De kamer zag er dik in orde uit bij aankomst. Toen we merkten dat onze tv en WiFi niet werkte, konden we de receptie makkelijk bereiken via WhatsApp. Er werd direct iemand gestuurd en na enkele pogingen om de tv te repareren, kwam de hotelmanager langs en stelde hij voor om ons te upgraden naar een betere kamer. Geweldige bedden en douches! Netflix op tv! Geweldige roomservice en geweldig restaurant waar het hotel mee samen werkt. Hier kan je heel de dag door gaan eten of eten bestellen en is allemaal super lekker! Ook het ontbijt via het hotel is zeer geslaagd! Wanneer ik terug naar Ubud kom, boek ik hier zeker opnieuw! 😍

text: Goed verblijf gehad bij Dinara Ubud. Het hotel is erg luxe en de kamers zijn werkelijk van alle gemakken voorzien. Het personeel is zeer vriendelijk en spreekt je aan bij je naam. title: хороший уютный отель

text:
Нашли это место по рекомендации друга , приехали сюда и влюбились !  Очень чистая территория и номера , в которых хочется оставаться. Для нас был важный критерий быстрый вайфай и место для йоги , все эти факторы были учтены 🔥 Также тут приветливый персонал, менеджер Ваян покорил нас своим сервисом !  
Помимо всех этих плюсов есть ещё бассейн , спа с доступным по цене и качественным массажем и вкусное кафе при отеле. Я в восторге !!!
title: Потрясающее место в Убуде

text: Посетили отель динара. Были приятно удивлены чистотой и доброжелательностью персонала . Вкусная еда , отличный сервис и вся инфраструктура присутствует у отеля . Это одно из лучших мест в которых мне довелось побывать в убуде . Я буду всем рекомендовать это место . Менеджер Ваян был услужлив , вежлив и очень приветлив . Благодарю весь персонал за приятное время проведённое в отеле . Руди и Вивик так же запомнились мне своей работой
title: Отличное место в убуде

text: все очень красиво и вкусная еда. Я заказала авокадо тост и ананасовый сок - принесли с очень красивой подачей. А также на заднем дворе есть красивый бассейн - глубокий с голубой водой и единорогами. Идеального дня 🙌
